alms, the following essays reveal the poets' consummate mastery of the demanding acrostic form and deserve incorporation in future discussions of biblical poetic art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aAcrostics in the Bible. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh1 aGeoghegan, Jeffrey C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNoel Freedman, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWelch, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781575065199zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781575065199423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781575065199.jpg  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK